NBC News' Chief Global Correspondent Bill Neely joins Ayman Mohyeldin and Yasmin Vossoughin to discuss why no deal was reached between President Trump and Kim Jong Un. Neely pins it to the leaders not being able to settle on a definition of denuclearization and the North Koreans wanting sanctions lifted. Bill Neely also adds that there was a lack of preparation on the US side.Feb. 28, 2019
